---
/**
 * Ordination Issue — the long-read page on full ordination for women:
 * overview, origins, movement timeline, videos, and further reading.
 * Address matches the old site: /ordination-issue.
 *
 * Two sections from the design (By Tradition, Scholarship) were hidden
 * in the mockup and are left out until the content is ready.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Ordination Issue · Sakyadhita"
  description="Full ordination for women — becoming a Bhikkhunī or Gelongma — has been one of the most contested issues in modern Buddhism. The history, milestones, and current state of the movement."
  active="resources"
  ogImage="/assets/bhutan-2025-ordination.png"
>
  <section class="ord-hero">
    <div class="content">
      <h1>Ordination issue</h1>
      <p>
        Full ordination for women — becoming a Bhikkhunī (Pali) or Gelongma (Tibetan) — has been
        one of the most contested issues in modern Buddhism. The picture in 2026 is dramatically
        different from even fifteen years ago, but it's uneven across schools, countries, and
        lineages.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="ord-hero-imgs">
      <figure><img src="/assets/1st-sakyadhita-conference-1987-dharamshala.png" alt="Participants of the first Sakyadhita conference, 1987" /></figure>
      <figure><img src="/assets/hero-2.png" alt="Buddhist nuns gathered in ceremony" style="object-position: 50% 30%;" /></figure>
      <figure><img src="/assets/hero-3.png" alt="Buddhist women in practice" /></figure>
      <figure><img src="/assets/bhutan-2025-ordination.png" alt="Nuns receiving full ordination in Bhutan, 2025" /></figure>
    </div>
    <p class="marquee-credit">
      For photos, special thanks to
      <a href="https://www.olivieradam.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Olivier Adam</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="onpage-nav">
    <div class="shell">
      <ul>
        <li><a class="is-active" href="#overview">Overview</a></li>
        <li><a href="#movement">The Movement</a></li>
        <li><a href="#watch">Videos</a></li>
        <li><a href="#see-also">See Also</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section id="overview">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="overview">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">OVERVIEW</div>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 12px;">Why this matters</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>
            Full ordination — taking the complete set of monastic vows as a <em>bhikkhuni</em>
            (Pali) or <em>bhiksuni</em> (Sanskrit) — is the deepest formal commitment a Buddhist
            woman can make to monastic life. For centuries, the path was open in some traditions
            and closed or interrupted in others.
          </p>
          <p>
            Since 1987, Sakyadhita has worked alongside scholars, monastics, and practitioners to
            restore and expand access to full ordination across all Buddhist traditions. The work
            is ongoing.
          </p>
          <div class="stats-3">
            <div class="s"><div class="num">2,000+</div><div class="lab">Theravada bhikkhunis today</div></div>
            <div class="s"><div class="num">29</div><div class="lab">Years since Theravada restoration</div></div>
            <div class="s"><div class="num">19</div><div class="lab">Conferences advancing the cause</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="origins">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="origins-split">
        <div class="origins-text">
          <div class="eyebrow">ORIGINS</div>
          <h2 class="h-section" style="margin-top: 8px;">Origins in ancient India</h2>
          <p style="margin-top: 18px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-body);">
            In the 6th century BCE, the Buddha affirmed the equal potential of women and men to
            achieve liberation. This affirmation represented a significant departure from
            prevailing views that defined women primarily in terms of their reproductive function
            and capacity for productive labor.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: 16px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-body);">
            The bhikkhuni sangha founded by Mahapajapati, the Buddha's aunt and foster mother, may
            have been the first monastic order for nuns in history. Since its inception, Buddhism
            has been unique in recognizing the equal spiritual potential of women and men.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: 16px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-body);">
            Despite this egalitarian philosophy, unequal social structures persist in most Buddhist
            cultures today. Today, the bhikkhuni sangha survives primarily in three traditions —
            Chinese, Korean, and Vietnamese — but efforts to establish or revive full ordination
            for women are underway in India, Indonesia, Sri Lanka, Thailand, and elsewhere.
          </p>
        </div>
        <figure class="origins-fig">
          <img
            src="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Prince_Siddhartha_with_his_maternal_aunt_Queen_Mahaprajapati_Gotami.JPG?width=700"
            alt="Prince Siddhartha with his foster mother Mahaprajapati, painting by Maligawage Sarlis"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>Painting by Maligawage Sarlis. Photo by MediaJet, 2009.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="movement" class="section--bg-subtle">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="eyebrow">THE MOVEMENT</div>
        <h2 class="h-section">Milestones in the restoration of full ordination</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="move-tl">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="year">1987</div>
          <div>
            <h3>The founding conversation</h3>
            <p>The first Sakyadhita conference in Bodh Gaya identifies women's ordination as the movement's signature issue.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="t-pic" style="background-image:url('/assets/founding-1987-bodhgaya.jpg');"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="year">1996</div>
          <div>
            <h3>The revival of bhikkhunī ordination in the Theravada tradition</h3>
            <p>Sri Lankan women ordained in Sarnath, India, marking the restoration of the Theravada bhikkhuni order.</p>
            <a class="link" href="https://present.bhikkhuni.net/bhikkhuni-kusuma/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display:inline-block; margin-top:10px; color:var(--purple); font-weight:600; font-size:14px;">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="t-pic" style="background-image:url('/assets/sarnath-1996-news.jpg'); background-position: center top;"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="year">1998</div>
          <div>
            <h3>International Full Ordination Ceremony in Bodhgaya, India</h3>
            <p>Bhiksunis Thubten Chodron and Karma Lekshe Tsomo were part of the bhikshuni sangha that gave dual ordination to new bhiksunis and bhikkhunis at Bodhgaya, India.</p>
            <a class="link" href="https://thubtenchodron.org/1998/02/restoring-bhikshuni-ordination/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display:inline-block; margin-top:10px; color:var(--purple); font-weight:600; font-size:14px;">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="t-pic" style="background-image:url('/assets/bodhgaya-1998-ordination.png');"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="year">2007</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Hamburg Congress</h3>
            <p>International congress on Buddhist women's role in the sangha, hosted by H.H. the Dalai Lama.</p>
            <a class="link" href="https://www.studienstiftung-fuer-buddhismus.de/en/abgeschlossene-projekte/1st-international-congress-on-buddhist-womens-role-in-the-sangha-2017/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display:inline-block; margin-top:10px; color:var(--purple); font-weight:600; font-size:14px;">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="t-pic" style="background-image:url('https://www.studienstiftung-fuer-buddhismus.de/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/MG_5010-copy-1024x683.jpg');"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="year">2022</div>
          <div>
            <h3>First bhikshuni ordination in Bhutan</h3>
            <p>At the King's request, Bhutan's Je Khenpo fully ordains 144 women — establishing a bhikshuni sangha within Tibetan Buddhism for the first time in modern history.</p>
            <a class="link" href="https://www.lionsroar.com/women-receive-full-ordination-in-bhutan-for-first-time-in-modern-history/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display:inline-block; margin-top:10px; color:var(--purple); font-weight:600; font-size:14px;">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="t-pic" style="background-image:url('https://www.lionsroar.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/feat-jun27.png');"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="year">2023</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Seoul Declaration</h3>
            <p>18th Sakyadhita conference participants reaffirm commitment to ordination work across all traditions.</p>
            <a class="link" href="https://www.buddhistdoor.net/features/daughters-of-the-buddha-18th-sakyadhita-conference-in-seoul-celebrates-the-sacred-feminine/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display:inline-block; margin-top:10px; color:var(--purple); font-weight:600; font-size:14px;">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="t-pic" style="background-image:url('/assets/seoul.png');"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="year">2025</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Second Bhutan ordination</h3>
            <p>At the culmination of Bhutan's Global Peace Prayer Festival, 265 nuns from ten countries receive full ordination — a profound step toward gender equality in spiritual leadership.</p>
            <a class="link" href="https://www.lionsroar.com/bhutan-festival-marks-landmark-for-buddhist-nuns/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display:inline-block; margin-top:10px; color:var(--purple); font-weight:600; font-size:14px;">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="t-pic" style="background-image:url('/assets/bhutan-2025-ordination.png');"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="watch">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="eyebrow">WATCH &amp; LEARN</div>
        <h2 class="h-section">Voices on full ordination</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="video-layout">
        <div class="video-main">
          <div class="video-frame">
            <iframe
              id="vid-player"
              src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/_j90nTgMs_Q?rel=0"
              title="Video player"
              allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
              allowfullscreen
            ></iframe>
          </div>
          <h3 class="now-title" id="vid-now-title">The Geshema is Born | Award-winning Film | Malati Rao</h3>
          <p class="now-desc" id="vid-now-desc">
            Malati Rao's award-winning documentary follows Tibetan Buddhist nuns who, empowered by
            His Holiness the Dalai Lama, become the first to receive the Geshema — the highest
            monastic degree, equivalent to a PhD.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="video-list" id="vid-list">
          <button
            class="vid-card active"
            data-id="_j90nTgMs_Q"
            data-title="The Geshema is Born | Award-winning Film | Malati Rao"
            data-desc="Malati Rao's award-winning documentary follows Tibetan Buddhist nuns who, empowered by His Holiness the Dalai Lama, become the first to receive the Geshema — the highest monastic degree, equivalent to a PhD."
          >
            <span class="thumb" style="background-image:url('https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_j90nTgMs_Q/hqdefault.jpg')"></span>
            <span class="v-body"><span class="v-title">The Geshema is Born | Award-winning Film | Malati Rao</span><span class="v-desc">Tibetan nuns earn the Geshema, Buddhism's highest monastic degree.</span></span>
          </button>
          <button
            class="vid-card"
            data-id="O10XPiF1wJw"
            data-title="Issues around the ordination of women in Buddhism"
            data-desc="A Q&A session from the 4th Global Conference in Perth (2006), organised by the Buddhist Society of Western Australia, addressing the questions surrounding women's ordination."
          >
            <span class="thumb" style="background-image:url('https://i.ytimg.com/vi/O10XPiF1wJw/hqdefault.jpg')"></span>
            <span class="v-body"><span class="v-title">Issues around the ordination of women in Buddhism</span><span class="v-desc">A 2006 Perth conference Q&amp;A on women's ordination.</span></span>
          </button>
          <button
            class="vid-card"
            data-id="yoNF0o3bDRQ"
            data-title="Fulfilling Buddha's Vision | Nuns seek equality through ordination (S1, E08) | 52 Documentary"
            data-desc="This documentary examines the reemergence of bhikkhunis — fully ordained female monastics — reclaiming their place in the Buddhist hierarchy some 1,000 years after nuns were last fully ordained."
          >
            <span class="thumb" style="background-image:url('https://i.ytimg.com/vi/yoNF0o3bDRQ/hqdefault.jpg')"></span>
            <span class="v-body"><span class="v-title">Fulfilling Buddha's Vision | Nuns seek equality through ordination (S1, E08) | 52 Documentary</span><span class="v-desc">The reemergence of fully ordained Buddhist nuns.</span></span>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="see-also" class="section--bg-subtle">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="overview">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">SEE ALSO</div>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 12px;">Further reading</h2>
          <p style="margin-top: 14px;">Background reading on full ordination, the movement's history, and the women who shaped it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="asp-grid">
          <a class="asp" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhikkhuni" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <h3>Bhikkhunī</h3>
            <p>The history, ordination, and modern revival of the order of fully ordained Buddhist nuns.</p>
            <span class="link">Read on Wikipedia →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="asp" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Congress_on_Buddhist_Women%27s_Role_in_the_Sangha" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <h3>1987 Bodhgaya Congress</h3>
            <p>The International Congress on Buddhist Women's Role in the Sangha, where Sakyadhita was founded.</p>
            <span class="link">Read on Wikipedia →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="asp" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Engaged_Buddhism" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <h3>Engaged Buddhism</h3>
            <p>Applying Buddhist teachings to social, political, economic, and environmental justice.</p>
            <span class="link">Read on Wikipedia →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="asp" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Women_in_Buddhism" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <h3>Women in Buddhism</h3>
            <p>An overview of women's roles, status, and contributions across the Buddhist traditions.</p>
            <span class="link">Read on Wikipedia →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="asp" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ayya_Khema" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <h3>Ayya Khema</h3>
            <p>The pioneering nun who helped convene the first Sakyadhita conference and founded monastic centres for women.</p>
            <span class="link">Read on Wikipedia →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    // ── Video switcher ──
    const list = document.getElementById('vid-list')
    const player = document.getElementById('vid-player') as HTMLIFrameElement | null
    const nowTitle = document.getElementById('vid-now-title')
    const nowDesc = document.getElementById('vid-now-desc')
    list?.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      const card = (e.target as Element).closest('.vid-card') as HTMLElement | null
      if (!card || !player) return
      list.querySelectorAll('.vid-card').forEach((c) => c.classList.remove('active'))
      card.classList.add('active')
      player.src = `https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/${card.dataset.id}?rel=0&autoplay=1`
      if (nowTitle) nowTitle.textContent = card.dataset.title || ''
      if (nowDesc) nowDesc.textContent = card.dataset.desc || ''
    })

    // ── On-page nav: smooth scroll + highlight section in view ──
    const nav = document.querySelector('.onpage-nav')
    if (nav) {
      document.documentElement.style.scrollBehavior = 'smooth'
      const navLinks = [...nav.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]')] as HTMLAnchorElement[]
      const sections: HTMLElement[] = []
      const linkFor = new Map<HTMLElement, HTMLAnchorElement>()
      navLinks.forEach((a) => {
        const sec = document.getElementById(a.getAttribute('href')!.slice(1))
        if (sec) {
          sections.push(sec)
          linkFor.set(sec, a)
          sec.style.scrollMarginTop = '140px'
        }
      })
      function update() {
        let active = sections[0]
        for (const sec of sections) {
          if (sec.getBoundingClientRect().top - 160 <= 0) active = sec
          else break
        }
        navLinks.forEach((a) => a.classList.remove('is-active'))
        if (active) linkFor.get(active)?.classList.add('is-active')
      }
      let raf: number | null = null
      const onScroll = () => {
        if (raf) return
        raf = requestAnimationFrame(() => {
          raf = null
          update()
        })
      }
      window.addEventListener('scroll', onScroll, { passive: true })
      window.addEventListener('resize', onScroll)
      update()
    }
  </script>

  <style is:global>
    .ord-hero {
      position: relative;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 36px 32px 50px;
      overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--bg-warm);
      text-align: center;
    }
    .ord-hero .content {
      position: relative;
      max-width: 820px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center;
    }
    .ord-hero h1 {
      font-family: var(--font-title); font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 40px; line-height: 1.1; color: var(--ink);
      margin: 0 0 16px; max-width: 18ch;
    }
    .ord-hero p {
      color: var(--ink-body); font-size: 18px;
      max-width: 62ch; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 auto 24px;
    }
    .ord-hero-imgs {
      max-width: 1320px;
      margin: 36px auto 0;
      padding: 0 32px;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .ord-hero-imgs figure {
      position: relative; margin: 0;
      height: 360px;
      border-radius: var(--r-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .ord-hero-imgs figure img {
      width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block;
    }
    .ord-hero .marquee-credit {
      margin-top: 24px;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 16px;
      color: #888888;
      padding-top: 8px;
      padding-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .ord-hero .marquee-credit a {
      color: #888888;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .ord-hero-imgs { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 8px; }
      .ord-hero-imgs figure { height: 300px; }
      .ord-hero p { font-size: 16px; }
    }
    @media (max-width: 520px) {
      .ord-hero-imgs { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 12px; padding: 0 20px; }
      .ord-hero-imgs figure { height: auto; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; }
    }

    /* Overview */
    .overview {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: 360px 1fr; gap: 64px; align-items: start;
    }
    .overview h2 { font-family: var(--font-title); font-weight: 700; font-size: 40px; line-height: 1.06; color: var(--ink); }
    .overview p { font-size: 16.5px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--ink-body); margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .overview .stats-3 {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px;
      margin-top: 28px; padding-top: 28px; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border);
    }
    .overview .stats-3 .s { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
    .overview .stats-3 .num { font-family: var(--font-num); font-weight: 700; font-size: 36px; color: var(--purple); line-height: 1; }
    .overview .stats-3 .lab { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--ink-2); text-transform: uppercase; }

    /* Origins split */
    .origins-split { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.35fr 0.65fr; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
    .origins-fig { margin: 0; }
    .origins-fig img { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; border-radius: var(--r-md); }
    .origins-fig figcaption { margin-top: 10px; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--ink-subtle); line-height: 1.4; }
    @media (max-width: 820px) {
      .origins-split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 28px; }
      .origins-fig { max-width: 320px; }
    }

    /* Movement timeline */
    .move-tl {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 32px;
      max-width: 880px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .move-tl::before {
      content: ""; position: absolute; left: 11px; top: 8px; bottom: 8px;
      width: 2px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--lavender-3), var(--coral-2));
      border-radius: 2px;
    }
    .step {
      position: relative;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 110px 1fr 220px;
      gap: 28px;
      padding: 18px 0;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .step::before {
      content: ""; position: absolute;
      left: -32px; top: 50%; transform: translateY(-50%);
      width: 24px; height: 24px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--bg);
      border: 3px solid var(--purple);
    }
    .step .year {
      font-family: var(--font-num);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 32px;
      color: var(--ink);
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .step h3 { font-family: var(--font-title); font-weight: 700; font-size: 22px; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .step p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--ink-body); line-height: 1.55; }
    .step .t-pic {
      align-self: center;
      border-radius: var(--r-md);
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: center;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      height: 150px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .step { grid-template-columns: 90px 1fr; }
      .step .t-pic { display: none; }
    }

    /* For aspirants / see-also cards */
    .asp-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
    .asp {
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--r-md);
      padding: 24px;
      display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px;
      transition: transform .15s, border-color .15s;
      text-decoration: none; color: inherit;
    }
    .asp:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); border-color: var(--lavender-2); }
    .asp h3 { font-family: var(--font-title); font-weight: 700; font-size: 22px; color: var(--ink); }
    .asp p { font-size: 14.5px; color: var(--ink-body); line-height: 1.55; }
    .asp .link { color: var(--purple); font-weight: 600; font-size: 14px; margin-top: auto; }

    /* Watch & learn */
    #watch { padding-top: 64px; padding-bottom: 112px; }
    .video-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.7fr 1fr; gap: 28px; align-items: stretch; }
    .video-main .video-frame {
      aspect-ratio: 16/9; width: 100%;
      border-radius: var(--r-md); overflow: hidden;
      background: #000; border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .video-main .video-frame iframe { width: 100%; height: 100%; border: 0; display: block; }
    .video-main .now-title {
